        {
          "renderType": "container",
          "maxWidth": "xs",
          "richTextStyles": true,
          "content": [
            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "h3",
              "content": "Wireframes"
            },
            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "p",
              "content": "We were ready to start wireframes. In this phase, the lead UX designer focused on the homepage, topics page, general layout and the main navigation. As mentioned earlier, elevating veterans' stories was important for this project which is why we decided to open with a quote from a veteran and feature the video sharing their stories prominently on the homepage. In terms of layout, the client, coming from the art world, encouraged us to use open and interesting layouts. This along with the restriction to leave images uncropped created asymmetrical and visually dynamic layouts. We were also encouraged to apply this to the topics page, which we did with a timeline style that also worked well for easy scanning and discoverability of topics. For the main navigation, we decided on a streamlined and sticky navigation bar for topics to be easily accessible to users as outlined in the requirements."
            }
          ]
        },
